<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-01-04T19:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-01-04T19:00:00-05:00" n="226" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d226">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">835.73/85: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the Ambassador in Argentina</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Stimson</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-01-04T19:00:00-05:00"><hi rend="italic">January 4,
                                        1919, 7 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>Your December 10, 4 p.m.</p>
                        <p>Continue to support project for extension of cables of Central and South
                            American Telegraph Company from Buenos Aires to Montevideo and again
                            acquaint the Argentine Government of the interest which the United
                            States Government has in such extension. Keep Department fully informed
                            as to probable result British Legation’s memorandum.</p>
                        <p>Department is considering advisability of taking up matter of British
                            protest with British Government.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Polk</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>